Quote:  Boiled flax-root water poured on the wounds,  and also dock-root (runa), well scraped and boiled, were our favourite remedies for gunshot and bayonet wounds. <i>IBid.</i> 2/396

Te Kaka was suffering agony from his shattered jaw; he had contrived to pound up some flax-root, and make a dressing of it, which he had tied under his terrible wound.
